author: Inside Edition
description:
Sponsored Content by RoC Skincare. 

Inside Edition teamed up with RoC® Skincare and its partner, dermatologist Dr. Sheila Farhang, for anti-aging tips. She says aging, lack of sunscreen and excessive and repeated movement can cause deep wrinkles in the neck. Dr. Farhang recommends RoC's Firming Serum Stick as an at-home, non-invasive lift for your face and neck.
title: Say Goodbye to Turkey Neck! Dermatologist Shares Her Top Anti-Aging Secret

author: Inside Edition
description: Outside Jimmy Kimmel's studio Thursday, supporters gathered to protest the show's suspension. When ABC pulled the plug on the show Wednesday night, it was a surprise to many. Some people believe Kimmel was suggesting Charlie Kirk's assassin was a MAGA supporter, which led to his suspension. On Wednesday, the chairman of the FCC, President Donald Trump appointee Brendan Carr, urged local ABC stations to "push back" against Kimmel. Shortly after, Jimmy Kimmel Live was suspended.
title: Outrage After ABC Suddenly Suspends Jimmy Kimmel Live

author: Inside Edition
description: First Lady Melania Trump and Princess Kate met kids in the scouts movement Thursday and joined in with arts and crafts projects. Melania sat on a kiddie chair, while Kate hunkered down on the lawn to crayon with the kids. Not surprisingly, the British weather was less than ideal. As Melania and President Donald Trump posed for pictures with the British prime minister and his wife, Melania's hair blew over her face. The historic state visit is on the front pages of British newspapers Thursday.
title: First Lady Melania And Princess Kate Join Together to Met Kids

author: Inside Edition
description: Popular comedian Guy Branum says he was told he was too fat to fly by an airline passenger and says the man assaulted him, leaving him with a bruise on his side. Branum stars on Apple TV's comedy series "Platonic" and has appeared on HBO's hit show "Hacks." Now he's making news for posting a video on the plane that shows him confronting the airline passenger. The other passenger denies assaulting Branum. Branum spoke with Inside Edition's Ann Mercogliano.
title: Comedian Guy Branum Says Passenger Told Him He Was Too Fat To Fly

author: Inside Edition
description: Crashing into a fire hydrant, the driver slammed through a wooden fence before plowing onto the patio of a home's backyard. The out of control vehicle continues to rev its engine after crashing into the home's living room. The frazzled homeowner appeared moments later and called police. Police arrested Nazim Useni, the suspected drunk driver. It's his 7th DUI-related offense. Homeowner Adam Dziubinski and his family were eating dinner when the crash happened just feet away.
title: Suspected Drunk Driver Crashes Into Home Just Feet Away From Family

author: Inside Edition
description: Two travel vloggers who thought they were flying to Nice, in the south of France, but got on a plane to Tunis, Tunisia, are visiting Tunis on purpose this time. On social media, they came under heat for being so desperate to leave the North African country, with many pointing out that Tunisia has beautiful beaches and a panoramic desert landscape. The two women spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall.
title: Vloggers Who Accidentally Flew To Tunisia Visit On Purpose This Time

author: Inside Edition
description: A New York middle schooler is accused of engaging in a sextortion campaign against his classmates since February. Police say they started to investigate when several victims came forward to their school resources officer at Fieldstone Middle School. The suspect is not being identified due to his age. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Middle Schooler Arrested for Alleged Sextortion Against Classmates: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: INSIDE EDITION is putting a piece of new technology to the test: an Anti-Fall Vest designed for the elderly. Every year, 1 in 4 Americans takes a bad spill, making falls the leading cause of injury-related deaths in the U.S. But now, this new device promises to cushion your fall with a motion-triggered airbag system that can detect when you’re falling. But does it work? Steven Fabian tried it out.
title: Will This Wearable Airbag Vest Protect You During A Fall?

title: School Vandals Turned In By Their Moms #shorts
